{"tid":1099561,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"華為喺巴基斯坦cctv系統裝wifi傳輸器 被員工發現 聲稱‘誤會’並拆咗佢","createTime":"2019-04-10T00:43:42.000Z","updateTime":"2019-04-10T05:25:52.000Z","uid":48083,"like":35,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":27,"replies":[{"pid":"707b1b8a9ad6d73641e1e4a3d3a1fa489311992c","tid":1099561,"uid":48083,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:43:42.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\"><strong>Huawei wi-fi modules were pulled from Pakistan CCTV system<br />\n<br />\nHuawei removed wi-fi transmitting cards from a Pakistan-based surveillance system's CCTV cabinets after they were discovered by the project's staff.<br />\n<br />\nPunjab Safe City Authority (PSCA) told BBC Panorama it had told the firm to remove the modules in 2017 &quot;due to [a] potential of misuse&quot;.</strong></span><br />\n<br />\nThe authority said that the Chinese firm had previously made mention of the cards in its bidding documents.<br />\n<br />\nBut a source involved in the project suggested the reference was obscure.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>A spokesman for Huawei said there had been a &quot;misunderstanding&quot;. He added that the cards had been installed to provide diagnostic information, but said he was unable to discuss the matter further.</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe PSCA confirmed that the explanation it had been given was that wi-fi connectivity could have made it easier for engineers to troubleshoot problems when they stood close to the cabinets, without having to open them up.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Two people involved in Lahore's project helped bring the matter to the BBC's attention and have asked to remain anonymous. O<span style=\"color: red;\"><span style=\"font-size: x-large;\">ne said that Huawei had never provided an app to make use of the wi-fi link, and added that the cabinets could already be managed remotely via the surveillance system's main network.</strong></span></span>"},{"pid":"b15aa9a28cebd9c75e2950822819cb98bb6fbeef","tid":1099561,"uid":48083,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:43:46.000Z","msg":"<strong> CCTV cabinet<br />\nIt was suggested that a wi-fi link could have helped engineers troubleshoot problems without having to climb up and open the cabinets<br />\nA UK-based cyber-security expert said that it was not uncommon for equipment sellers to install extra gear to let them offer additional services at a later date.<br />\n<br />\nBut he added that the affair highlighted the benefit of oversight because if the authority had remained unaware of the cards' existence, it could not have taken steps to manage any potential risk they posed.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;As soon as you give someone another method of remote connectivity you give them a method to attack it,&quot; commented Alan Woodward.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;If you put a wi-fi card in then you're potentially giving someone some other form of remote access to it. You might say it's done for one purpose, but as soon as you do that it's got the potential to be misused.&quot;<br />\n</strong><br />\nThere is no evidence that the cards created a vulnerability, and one of the sources involved confirmed that there had not been an opportunity to test if they could be exploited before the kit was removed.<br />\n<br />\n'Prompt response'<br />\n<br />\nLahore's Safe City scheme was first announced in 2016 following a series of terrorist bombings.<br />\n<br />\nIt provides a vast surveillance network of cameras and other sensors, and a brand new communications system for the city's emergency services⋯⋯⋯<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/amp/technology-47856098?__twitter_impression=true\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Famp%2Ftechnology-47856098%3F__twitter_impression%3Dtrue&d=se%2BVxgw3JrdCjNobn1OhImo8q5%2FbnpuKyKF%2Fs7IAglk%3D&h=3a7a0153\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Famp%2Ftechnology-47856098%3F__twitter_impression%3Dtrue&h=3428d45c\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.bbc.com/news/amp/technology-47856098?__twitter_impression=true</a>"},{"pid":"95943ae43c50050f6eea39efbd09c0065690828f","tid":1099561,"uid":57376,"like":74,"dislike":0,"score":74,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:45:23.000Z","msg":"連所謂最堅實盟友都信唔過要裝彈弓<br />\n我睇遲早無埋<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c413594f67c2e4f137436c6dade747af6946e2da","tid":1099561,"uid":40763,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:46:41.000Z","msg":"搵人send俾德國 意大利睇啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"1d0572f7aa0e5898178b4586e515d44f5d05216f","tid":1099561,"uid":116289,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:48:42.000Z","msg":"又詐詐諦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/dead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a3ae5a67b4a33609337285cd46725c5d033f7ad5","tid":1099561,"uid":62646,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:49:15.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"b2bbcaabd73ae5c745a16921dc21a0111feb4d7d","tid":1099561,"uid":808,"like":2,"dislike":65,"score":-63,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:51:08.000Z","msg":"美國夠竊聽啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"36ef7bb221c8c496155cf86001d744adcd05159e","tid":1099561,"uid":2757,"like":17,"dislike":0,"score":17,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:59:17.000Z","msg":"沒事兒... 沒事兒... 誤會來的... 誤會來的..."},{"pid":"8cef47714799f90a0c53b04cb6d22d8fbd43ca7a","tid":1099561,"uid":3457,"like":62,"dislike":0,"score":62,"quote":{"pid":"b2bbcaabd73ae5c745a16921dc21a0111feb4d7d","tid":1099561,"uid":808,"like":2,"dislike":65,"score":-63,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-04-10T00:51:08.000Z","msg":"美國夠竊聽啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/z.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"